headline: Citi Sees Equities Boost From Fed Cuts, No US Recession
summary: Citigroup's Beata Manthey discusses the outlook for equity markets, saying that the prospect of Federal Reserve interest-rate cuts and the US avoiding recession bodes well for "all the major indices." Speaking on Bloomberg Television, Manthey also comments on Citi's overweight stance on European banks and how to play the artificial intelligence theme in Europe.
